title: Trump set to stand trial during election primaries
description: Donald Trump's election interference trial could start a day before a key date in the Republican primaries, according to court documents.

title: Trio booked flights to Pakistan a day before Surrey girl's body found
description: Three people known to Sara Sharif flew to Pakistan the day before the 10-year-old's body was discovered by police.

title: 'Special, special night': How victorious Lionesses celebrated semi-final win
description: England's Lionesses danced in the dressing room as they celebrated reaching their first ever Women's World Cup final with a 3-1 win over hosts Australia.

title: Six tourists arrested over alleged rape of British teenager on Spanish holiday island
description: Six people have been arrested over the alleged rape of an 18-year-old British woman on the Spanish holiday island of Majorca.

title: Lionesses through to their first World Cup final after sensational 3-1 win over hosts Australia
description: England's Lionesses have reached the final of the Women's World Cup after beating Australia 3-1 in a thrilling semi-final.

title: Germany approves landmark bill to liberalise cannabis use and sale
description: Being in possession of small amounts of cannabis is on its way to becoming legal in Germany after the country's cabinet approved a plan to begin decriminalising the drug.

title: Wildfires burn in Tenerife, Canada and Portugal amid warning of 'alarming' speed of climate change
description: Wildfires raging across the world and record heatwaves are "really alarming" evidence of the speed of climate change, Europe's top space official has said.

title: The Killers apologise after being booed for bringing Russian fan on stage
description: The Killers have issued an apology after lead singer Brandon Flowers was booed for bringing a Russian fan on stage to play the drums at a concert in Georgia.

title: Mother found guilty of murdering her three daughters
description: A mother has been found guilty of murder after smothering her three daughters to death in New Zealand.

title: Quarter of world's population living with extreme annual water stress
description: A quarter of the world's population is currently exposed to extremely high annual water stress, according to new data from the World Resources Institute (WRI).

title: At least 106 killed in Hawaii wildfires - and children among victims yet to be identified
description: The blaze that burned through the historic town of Lahaina on Maui last week has killed at least 106 people, Hawaii's governor has said.

title: Banking glitch 'allows customers with no money to withdraw funds from ATM'
description: A glitch with Bank of Ireland's online app reportedly allowed customers with no money to transfer funds and withdraw it from an ATM.

title: 'Why'd it have to be snakes?' - New species of serpent named after Harrison Ford
description: A new species of snake has been named after Harrison Ford.

title: England v Australia: Lionesses set to roar as they attempt to reach first ever World Cup final
description: Hot on the heels of a blockbuster Ashes series, England fans are in for another high stakes sporting clash with Australia as the Lionesses take on the Matildas in the Women’s World Cup semi-final.
